# idastone/.env.example — committed template
#
# Copy to ".env" and fill in real values. The .env file is gitignored
# (see .gitignore and install-assets/gitignore.idastone) so your keys
# never touch git. If you edit install.sh or schema to add new env
# vars, document them here too.
#
# To load these vars in your shell (POSIX-compatible):
#   set -a; . .env; set +a
# Any script idastone runs in that shell session inherits them.

# ─── GPU provisioning mode ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# router  — idastone's cross-provider router (default; uses the per-provider
#           keys below). Set this if you want autonomous provisioning across
#           RunPod/Vast/Prime/Verda.
# custom  — bring your own GPU setup (own AWS account, on-prem cluster, SSH
#           tunnel to a workstation, university quota, etc.). The router is
#           bypassed; the agent runs the /gpu-custom-setup skill on first
#           GPU need and saves your flow to .claude/gpu-custom.md.
# none    — no GPU layer at all (running idastone for non-GPU research).
IDASTONE_GPU_MODE=router

# ─── GPU providers (router mode only) ────────────────────────────────────
# `scripts/gpu.py` is the cross-provider router. It auto-discovers every
# provider whose env var is set below. Configuring 2+ unlocks preemption
# survivability (router hops on OutOfStock/BidRejected); 3+ unlocks
# arbitrage. Single-provider also works — autonomous runs just lose the
# survivability story.
#
# `docs/providers-setup.md` has the per-provider account-setup checklists
# (signup URLs, billing prerequisites, SSH key registration, verification
# curls). Read that before you copy keys in.

# RunPod — https://www.runpod.io/console/user/settings → API Keys
# Used by: gpu.py + scripts/runpod.py (legacy single-provider CLI)
RUNPOD_API_KEY=

# Vast.ai — https://cloud.vast.ai/account/ → API Keys → Generate New
# Note: instance creation requires billing/credits at https://cloud.vast.ai/billing/
# (search/list/price work on an empty account; create returns insufficient_credit).
VAST_API_KEY=

# Prime Intellect — https://app.primeintellect.ai/dashboard/tokens → Generate New Key
# Note: also needs an SSH key UUID — upload your public key at
# https://app.primeintellect.ai/dashboard/ssh-keys, then paste the
# returned id below. Create requires billing/credits at the dashboard.
PRIME_API_KEY=
PRIME_SSH_KEY_ID=

# Verda Cloud (formerly DataCrunch) — https://cloud.verda.com/account-settings/api
# OAuth2 client_credentials flow, NOT a static API key. Generate a client_id
# and client_secret pair in the dashboard. Adapter mints a JWT bearer token
# from /v1/oauth2/token and refreshes it as needed.
# Also requires a pre-registered SSH key UUID — upload your pubkey via the
# dashboard or POST /v1/ssh-keys, then paste the UUID below.
DATACRUNCH_CLIENT_ID=
DATACRUNCH_CLIENT_SECRET=
DATACRUNCH_SSH_KEY_ID=

# ─── ntfy push notifications (scripts/notify.sh) ─────────────────────────
# Generate a non-guessable topic: `openssl rand -hex 16`
# See docs/ntfy-setup.md for phone-side setup.
NTFY_TOPIC=
# NTFY_SERVER=https://ntfy.sh   # optional; default is public ntfy.sh

# ─── Model-provider keys (if you use alternate LLMs in /deploy-team) ─────
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=        # only if running outside Claude Code
